The FDA is quoted as saying that it "...continues to believe that the current safety limits for cellphone radiofrequency energy exposure remain acceptable for protecting the public health."<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://smartmobtech.com/news/5g-what-is-it-and-how-will-it-help-us/ |title=What is 5G |access-date=July 29, 2019 }}</ref>

During the [[COVID-19 pandemic]], misinformation circulated claiming that 5G networks contribute to the spread of COVID-19.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Gallagher |first1=Ryan |title=5G Virus Conspiracy Theory Fueled by Coordinated Effort |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2020-04-09/covid-19-link-to-5g-technology-fueled-by-coordinated-effort |access-date=12 April 2020 |work=[[Bloomberg News]] |date=9 April 2020}}</ref>
